obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (39151)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39151&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Assam Reorganisation`
  line `(Meghalaya) Act, 1969.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint:`
  line
  line `Provided that different dates may be appointed for different provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 12th January, 1970, vide notification No. G.S.R. 74, 12th January, 1970, in respect of sections 2 and 3, see Gazette of India,`
  line `Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(i).`
  line
  line `30th January, 1970, vide notification No. G.S.R. 182, dated 30th January, 1970, in respect of sections 11, 12, 13, 16, 17, 28,`
  line `29, 62, 73 and 77, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(i).`
  line
  line `25th February, 1970, vide notification No. G.S.R. 310, dated 25th February, in respect of sections 11, 12, 13, 16, 17, 28, 29,`
  line `62, 73 and 77 1970, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(i).`
  line
  line `2nd April, 1970, vide notification No. G.S.R. 493, dated 2th March, 1970, in respect of the provisions (other than those which`
  line `have already been brought into force), see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(i).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (39152)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39152&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,—`
  line
  line `(a) "appointed day" means such date as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint for the formation of the autonomous State;`
  line
  line `(b) "article" means an article of the Constitution;`
  line
  line `(c) "autonomous State" means the autonomous State of Meghalaya formed under section 3;`
  line
  line `(d) "constituency" means a territorial constituency provided by order made under section 12 for`
  line `the purpose of election to the Legislative Assembly;`
  line
  line `(e) "Election Commission" means the Election Commission appointed by the President under`
  line `article 324;`
  line
  line `(f) "Governor" means the Governor of Assam exercising his functions as Governor in relation to`
  line `Meghalaya by virtue of this Act;`
  line
  line `(g) "law" includes any enactment, Ordinance, regulation, order, bye-law, rule, scheme,`
  line `notification or other instrument, having immediately before the appointed day, the force of law in the`
  line `whole or in any part of the autonomous State;`
  line
  line `(h) "Legislative Assembly" means the Legislative Assembly of Meghalaya;`
  line
  line `(i) "Meghalaya" means the autonomous State referred to in section 3;`
  line
  line `(j) "member" means a member of the Legislative Assembly;`
  line
  line `(k) "Official Gazette" means the Official Gazette of Meghayala or the Gazette of India; and`
  line
  line `(l) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (39153)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Formation of Meghalaya.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39153&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) On and from the appointed day, there shall be formed within the`
  line `State of Assam an autonomous State to be known as Meghalaya which shall, subject to the provisions of`
  line `sub-section (2), comprise the following tribal areas, namely:—`
  line
  line `(i) The United Khasi Jaintia Hills District as described in sub-paragraph (2) of paragraph 20 of`
  line `the Sixth Schedule to the Constitution (exclusive of the proviso thereto) but excluding the areas`
  line `transferred to the Mikir Hills autonomous district by the notification of the Government of Assam`
  line `No. TAD/R/31/50/149 dated the 13th April, 1951, and`
  line
  line `(ii) the Garo Hills District specified in Part A of the table appended to paragraph 20 aforesaid.`
  line
  line `(2) If, before such date as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, fix for`
  line `the purpose not being a date later than the appointed day, the District Council for the autonomous district`
  line `of the North Cachar Hills or the Mikir Hills or both, as the case may be, has or have by resolution passed`
  line `by a majority of not less than two-thirds of the members thereof, expressed a desire that the said`
  line `autonomous district or districts shall form part of Meghalaya, the President may, by order, make a`
  line `declaration to that effect and accordingly, on and from the appointed day, the North Cachar Hills District`
  line `or the Mikir Hills District or both, as the case may be, shall also form part of Meghalaya.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (39154)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Executive power of Meghalaya.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39154&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The executive power of Meghalaya shall be vested in the`
  line `Governor and shall be exercised by him either directly or through officers subordinate to him in`
  line `accordance with this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in this section shall—`
  line
  line `(a) be deemed to transfer to the Governor any functions conferred by any existing law on any`
  line `other authority; or`
  line
  line `(b) prevent Parliament or the Legislature of the State of Assam or Meghalaya from conferring by`
  line `law functions on any authority subordinate to the Governor.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (39155)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Extent of executive power of Meghalaya.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39155&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the executive`
  line `power of Meghalaya shall extend to the matters with respect to which the Legislature of Meghalaya has`
  line `power to make laws:`
  line
  line `Provided that in any matter with respect to which the Legislature of Meghalaya, the Legislature of the`
  line `State of Assam and Parliament have power to make laws, the executive power of Meghalaya shall be`
  line `subject to, and limited by, the executive power expressly conferred by this Act, or by any law made by`
  line `Parliament upon the Union or the State of Assam or the authorities thereof or, as the case may be, by the`
  line `Legislature of the State of Assam upon the State of Assam or authorities thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) On and from the appointed day, the executive power of the State of Assam shall not extend, in`
  line `relation to Meghalaya to the matters with respect to which the Legislature of Meghalaya has exclusive`
  line `power to make laws under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that, save as otherwise provided in this Act, the`
  line `executive power of the State of Assam shall, in relation to Meghalaya, continue to extend to the matters`
  line `with respect to which the Legislature of Meghalaya has no power to make laws.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (39156)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Council of Ministers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39156&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be a Council of Ministers with the Chief Minister at the`
  line `head to aid and advice the Governor in the exercise of his functions in relation to Meghalaya.`
  line
  line `(2) The question whether any, and if so, what, advice was tendered by Ministers to the Governor shall`
  line `not be inquired into in any court.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (39157)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Other provisions as to Ministers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39157&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chief Minister shall be appointed by the Governor`
  line `and the other Ministers shall be appointed by the Governor on the advice of the Chief Minister, and the`
  line `Ministers shall hold office during the pleasure of the Governor.`
  line
  line `(2) The Council of Ministers shall be collectively responsible to the Legislative Assembly.`
  line
  line `(3) Before a Minister enters upon his office, the Governor shall administer to him the oaths of office`
  line `and of secrecy according to the form set out for this purpose in the First Schedule.`
  line
  line `(4) A Minister who for any period of six consecutive months is not a member of the`
  line `Legislative Assembly shall at the expiration of that period cease to be a Minister.`
  line
  line `(5) The salaries and allowances of Ministers shall be such as the Legislature of Meghalaya may from`
  line `time to time by law determine and, until the Legislature so determines, shall be determined by the`
  line Governor.
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (39158)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Advocate-General for Meghalaya.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39158&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Governor may, if he thinks fit to do so, appoint a`
  line `person who is qualified to be appointed a Judge of a High Court to be Advocate-General for Meghalaya.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall be the duty of the Advocate-General to give advice to the Government of Meghalaya upon`
  line `such legal matters, and to perform such other duties of a legal character as may, from time to time, be`
  line `referred or assigned to him by the Governor, and to discharge the functions conferred on him by or under`
  line `this Act or any other law for the time being in force.`
  line
  line `(3) The Advocate-General shall hold office during the pleasure of the Governor, and shall receive`
  line `such remuneration as the Governor may determine.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (39159)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Conduct of business.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39159&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) All executive actions of the Government of Meghalaya shall be`
  line `expressed to be taken in the name of the Governor.`
  line
  line `(2) Orders and other instruments made and executed in the name of the Governor shall be`
  line `authenticated in such manner as may be specified in rules to be made by the Governor, and the validity of`
  line `an order or instrument which is so authenticated shall not be called in question on the ground that it is not`
  line `an order or instrument made or executed by the Governor.`
  line
  line `(3) The Governor shall make rules for the more convenient transaction of the business of the`
  line `Government of Meghalaya and for the allocation among Ministers of the said business.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (39160)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Duties of Chief Minister as respects the furnishing of information to Governor, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39160&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `It shall`
  line `be the duty of the Chief Minister of Meghalaya—`
  line
  line `(a) to communicate to the Governor all decisions of the Council of Ministers relating to the`
  line `administration of the affairs of Meghalaya and proposals for legislation;`
  line
  line `(b) to furnish such information relating to the administration of the affairs of Meghalaya and`
  line `proposals for legislation as the Governor may call for; and`
  line
  line `(c) if the Governor so requires, to submit for the consideration of the Council of Ministers any`
  line `matter on which a decision has been taken by a Minister but which has not been considered by the`
  line Council.
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (39161)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Constitution of the Legislature of Meghalaya.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39161&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be a Legislature for Meghalaya`
  line `which shall consist of the Governor and the Legislative Assembly.`
  line
  line `(2) The total number of seats in the Legislative Assembly to be filled by persons chosen by direct`
  line `election from constituencies in Meghalaya shall be fixed by the Central Government by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette after consultation with the Election Commission, but shall not be less than thirty-five or`
  line `more than fifty-five.`
  line
  line `(3) The Governor may, if he is of opinion that any minority communities in Meghalaya need`
  line `representation in the Legislative Assembly and are not adequately represented therein, nominate not more`
  line `than three members of such communities, not being persons in the service of the Government, to the`
  line `Legislative Assembly.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (39162)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Delimitation of constituencies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39162&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Election Commission shall, in the manner herein`
  line `provided, distribute the total number of seats in the Legislative Assembly as fixed under sub-section (2)`
  line `of section 11 to single member constituencies and delimit them on the basis of the latest census figures`
  line `having regard to the following provisions, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) all constituencies shall, as far as practicable, consist of geographically compact areas, and in`
  line `delimiting them, regard shall be had to the physical features, existing boundaries of administrative`
  line `units, facilities of communication and public convenience;`
  line
  line `(b) every constituency shall be so delimited as to fall only within an Assembly constituency of the`
  line `Legislative Assembly of the State of Assam;`
  line
  line `(c) the population of each constituency shall, as far as practicable, be the same throughout`
  line Meghalaya.
  line
  line `(2) For the purpose of assisting the Election Commission in the performance of its functions under`
  line `this section, the Commission shall associate with itself such number of associate members not exceeding`
  line `five as the Governor may nominate to represent Meghalaya:`
  line
  line `Provided that none of the associate members shall have a right to vote or to sign any decision of the`
  line `Election Commission.`
  line
  line `(3) If owing to death or resignation, the office of an associate member falls vacant, it shall be filled as`
  line `soon as may be practicable by the Governor in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(4) The Election Commission shall—`
  line
  line `(a) publish its proposals for the delimitation of constituencies, together with the dissenting`
  line `proposals, if any, of any associate member who desires publication thereof, in the Official Gazette`
  line `and in such other manner as the Commission may consider fit, together with a notice inviting`
  line `objections and suggestions in relation to the proposals and specifying a date on or after which the`
  line `proposals will be further considered by it;`
  line
  line `(b) consider all objections and suggestions which may have been received by it before the date so`
  line `specified, and for the purpose of such consideration hold one or more public sittings at such place or`
  line `places as it may think fit;`
  line
  line `(c) after considering all objections and suggestions which may have been received by it before the`
  line `date so specified, determine by one or more orders the delimitation of constituencies and cause such`
  line `order or orders to be published in the Official Gazette; and upon such publication, the order or orders`
  line `shall have the full force of law and shall not be called in question in any court.`
  line
  line `(5) As soon as may be after such publication, every such order shall be laid before the`
  line `Legislative Assembly.`
  line
  line `(6) Upon the completion of each census, the total number of seats in the Legislative Assembly and the`
  line `division of Meghalaya into territorial constituencies shall be readjusted by such authority and in such`
  line `manner as Parliament may by law determine:`
  line
  line `Provided that such readjustment shall not affect representation in the Legislative Assembly until the`
  line `dissolution of the then existing Assembly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—In this section, "latest census figures" mean the census figures with respect to`
  line `Meghalaya ascertainable from the latest census of which the finally published figures are available.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (39163)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Power of Election Commission to maintain delimitation orders up-to-date.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39163&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Election`
  line `Commission may, from time to time by notification in the Official Gazette,—`
  line
  line `(a) correct any printing mistake in any order made under section 12 or any error arising therein`
  line `from inadvertent slip or omission;`
  line
  line `(b) where the boundaries or name of any territorial division mentioned in any such order are or is`
  line `altered, make such amendments as appear to it to be necessary or expedient for bringing such order`
  line up-to-date.
  line
  line `(2) Every notification under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is issued, before the`
  line `Legislative Assembly.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (39164)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Electors and electoral rolls.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39164&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) The persons entitled to vote at an election of members shall be`
  line `the persons entitled by virtue of the provisions of the Constitution and the Representation of the People`
  line `Act, 1950 (43 of 1950) to be registered as voters at elections to the House of the People.`
  line
  line `(2) The electoral roll for every constituency shall consist of so much of the electoral roll for an`
  line `Assembly constituency of the Legislative Assembly of the State of Assam as relates to the areas`
  line `comprised within each such constituency and it shall not be necessary to prepare or revise separately the`
  line `electoral roll for any such constituency.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (39165)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Right to vote.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39165&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `Every person, whose name is for the time being entered in the electoral roll for a`
  line `constituency, shall be entitled to vote at the election of a member from that constituency.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (39166)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Qualification for membership.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39166&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `A person shall not be qualified to be chosen to fill a seat in the`
  line `Legislative Assembly unless he—`
  line
  line `(a) is a citizen of India and makes and subscribes before some person authorised in that behalf by`
  line `the Election Commission an oath or affirmation according to the form set out for the purpose in the`
  line `First Schedule;`
  line
  line `(b) is not less than twenty-five years of age; and`
  line
  line `(c) is an elector in any constituency in Meghalaya.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (39167)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Election to the Legislative Assembly.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39167&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of Part I, Chapters III and IV of Part II`
  line `and Parts III to XI of the Representation of the People Act, 1951 (43 of 1951), and of any rules and orders`
  line `made thereunder for the time being in force, shall apply to and in relation to the elections to the`
  line `Legislative Assembly of Meghalaya as they apply to and in relation to an election to the`
  line `Legislative Assembly of a State, subject to such modifications as the President may, after consultation`
  line `with the Election Commission, by order, direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (39168)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Duration of Legislative Assembly.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39168&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `The Legislative Assembly, unless sooner dissolved, shall`
  line `continue for five years from the date appointed for its first meeting and no longer, and the expiration of`
  line `the said period of five years shall operate as a dissolution of the Legislative Assembly:`
  line
  line `Provided that the said period may, while a Proclamation of Emergency issued under clause (1) of`
  line `article 352 is in operation, be extended by Parliament by law for a period not exceeding one year at a time`
  line `and not extending in any case beyond a period of six months after the Proclamation has ceased to operate.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (39169)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Sessions of Legislative Assembly, prorogation and dissolution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39169&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Governor shall, from`
  line `time to time summon the Legislative Assembly to meet at such time and place as he thinks fit, but six`
  line `months shall not intervene between its last sitting in one session and the date appointed for its first sitting`
  line `in the next session.`
  line
  line `(2) The Governor may, from time to time,—`
  line
  line `(a) prorogue the Legislative Assembly;`
  line
  line `(b) dissolve the Legislative Assembly.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (39170)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Right of Governor to address and send messages to Legislative Assembly.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39170&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Governor`
  line `may address the Legislative Assembly and may for that purpose require the attendance of members.`
  line
  line `(2) The Governor may send messages to the Legislative Assembly, whether with respect to a Bill then`
  line `pending in the Legislative Assembly or otherwise and when a message is so sent, the Legislative`
  line `Assembly shall with all convenient despatch consider any matter required by the message to be taken into`
  line consideration.
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (39171)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Special address by the Governor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39171&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) At the commencement of the first session after each`
  line `general election to the Legislative Assembly and at the commencement of the first session of each year,`
  line `the Governor shall address the Legislative Assembly and inform the Assembly of the causes of its`
  line summons.
  line
  line `(2) Provision shall be made by the rules regulating the procedure of the Legislative Assembly for the`
  line `allotment of time for discussion of the matters referred to in such address.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (39172)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Rights of Ministers as respects Legislative Assembly.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39172&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `Every Minister and the`
  line `Advocate-General for Meghalaya shall have the right to speak in, and otherwise to take part in the`
  line `proceedings of, the Legislative Assembly, and to speak in, and otherwise to take part in the proceedings`
  line `of, any committee of the Legislative Assembly of which he may be named a member, but shall not, by`
  line `virtue of this section, be entitled to vote.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (39173)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Speaker and Deputy Speaker of Legislative Assembly.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39173&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Legislative Assembly shall, as`
  line `soon as may be, choose two members of the Assembly to be respectively Speaker and Deputy Speaker`
  line `thereof, and, so often as the office of Speaker or Deputy Speaker becomes vacant, the Assembly shall`
  line `choose another member to be Speaker or Deputy Speaker, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) A member holding office as Speaker or Deputy Speaker of the Legislative Assembly—`
  line
  line `(a) shall vacate his office if he ceases to be a member of the Assembly;`
  line
  line `(b) may at any time by writing under his hand addressed, if such member is the Speaker, to the`
  line `Deputy Speaker, and if such member is the Deputy Speaker, to the Speaker, resign his office; and`
  line
  line `(c) may be removed from his office by a resolution of the Legislative Assembly passed by a`
  line `majority of all the then members of the Assembly:`
  line
  line `Provided that no resolution for the purpose of clause (c) shall be moved unless at least fourteen days'`
  line `notice has been given of the intention to move the resolution:`
  line
  line `Provided further that whenever the Legislative Assembly is dissolved, the Speaker shall not vacate his`
  line `office until immediately before the first meeting of the Assembly after the dissolution.`
  line
  line `(3) While the office of Speaker is vacant, the duties of the office shall be performed by the`
  line `Deputy Speaker or, if the office of Deputy Speaker is also vacant, by such member of the Legislative`
  line `Assembly as the Governor may appoint for the purpose.`
  line
  line `(4) During the absence of the Speaker from any sitting of the Legislative Assembly, the`
  line `Deputy Speaker or, if he is also absent, such person as may be determined by the rules of procedure of the`
  line `Legislative Assembly, or, if no such person is present, such other person as may be determined by the`
  line `Legislative Assembly, shall act as Speaker.`
  line
  line `(5) There shall be paid to the Speaker and the Deputy Speaker of the Legislative Assembly such`
  line `salaries and allowances as may be respectively fixed by the Legislature of Meghalaya by law and, until`
  line `provision in that behalf is so made, such salaries and allowances as the Governor may, by order,`
  line determine.
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (39228)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Speaker and Deputy Speaker not to preside while`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39228&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) At any sitting of the Legislative Assembly while any resolution for the`
  line `removal of the Speaker from his office is under consideration, the Speaker, or, while any resolution for`
  line `the removal of the Deputy Speaker from his office is under consideration, the Deputy Speaker, shall not,`
  line `though he is present, preside, and the provisions of sub-section (4) of section 23 shall apply in relation to`
  line `every such sitting as they apply in relation to a sitting from which the Speaker or, as the case may be, the`
  line `Deputy Speaker is absent.`
  line
  line `(2) The Speaker shall have the right to speak in, and otherwise to take part in the proceedings of, the`
  line `Legislative Assembly while any resolution for his removal from office is under consideration in the`
  line `Legislative Assembly and shall, notwithstanding anything in section 27, be entitled to vote only in the`
  line `first instance on such resolution or on any other matter during such proceedings but not in the case of an`
  line `equality of votes.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (39175)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Secretariat of Legislative Assembly.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39175&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Legislative Assembly shall have a separate`
  line `secretarial staff.`
  line
  line `(2) The Legislature of Meghalaya may by law regulate the recruitment, and the conditions of service`
  line `of persons appointed, to the secretarial staff of the Legislative Assembly.`
  line
  line `(3) Until provision is made by the Legislature of Meghalaya under sub-section (2), the Governor may,`
  line `after consultation with the Speaker of the Legislative Assembly, make rules regulating the recruitment,`
  line `and the conditions of service of persons appointed, to the secretarial staff of the Legislative Assembly,`
  line `and any rules so made shall have effect subject to the provisions of any law made under the said`
  line sub-section.
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (39176)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Oath or affirmation by members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39176&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `Every member of the Legislative Assembly shall, before`
  line `taking his seat, make and subscribe before the Governor, or some person appointed in that behalf by him,`
  line `an oath or affirmation according to the form set out for the purpose in the First Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (39177)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Voting in Assembly, power of Assembly to act notwithstanding vacancies and quorum.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39177&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise provided in this Act, all questions at any sitting of the`
  line `Legislative Assembly shall be determined by majority of votes of the members present and voting other`
  line `than the Speaker or person acting as such.`
  line
  line `(2) The Speaker or person acting as such shall not vote in the first instance, but shall have and`
  line `exercise a casting vote in the case of an equality of votes.`
  line
  line `(3) The Legislative Assembly shall have power to act notwithstanding any vacancy in the`
  line `membership thereof, and any proceedings in the Legislative Assembly shall be valid notwithstanding that`
  line `it is discovered subsequently that some person who was not entitled so to do sat or voted or otherwise`
  line `took part in the proceedings.`
  line
  line `(4) Until the Legislature of Meghalaya by law otherwise provides, the quorum to constitute a meeting`
  line `of the Legislative Assembly shall be ten members.`
  line
  line `(5) If at any time during a meeting of the Legislative Assembly there is no quorum, it shall be the`
  line `duty of the Speaker or person acting as such either to adjourn the Assembly or suspend the meeting until`
  line `there is a quorum.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (39178)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Vacation of seats.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39178&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall be a member of Parliament or of the`
  line `Legislative Assembly of the State of Assam and also of the Legislative Assembly of Meghalaya, and if a`
  line `person is chosen a member of Parliament or of the Legislative Assembly of Assam and also of the`
  line `Legislative Assembly of Meghalaya, then, at the expiration of such period, as may be specified in rules`
  line `made by the President, that persons seat in Parliament or, as the case may be, in the`
  line `Legislative Assembly of Assam, shall become vacant unless he has previously resigned his seat in the`
  line `Legislative Assembly of Meghalaya.`
  line
  line `(2) If a member of the Legislative Assembly—`
  line
  line `(a) becomes subject to any of the disqualifications mentioned in section 29, or`
  line
  line `(b) resigns his seat by writing under his hand addressed to the Speaker,`
  line
  line `his seat shall thereupon become vacant.`
  line
  line `(3) If for a period of sixty days a member of the Legislative Assembly is, without permission of the`
  line `Legislative Assembly, absent from all meetings thereof, the Assembly may declare his seat vacant:`
  line
  line `Provided that in computing the said period of sixty days no account shall be taken of any period`
  line `during which the Legislative Assembly is prorogued or is adjourned for more than four consecutive days.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (39179)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Disqualifications for membership.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39179&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person shall be disqualified for being chosen as, and`
  line `for being, a member of the Legislative Assembly,—`
  line
  line `(a) if he holds any office of profit under the Government of India or the Government of any State`
  line `or the Government of Meghalaya other than an office declared by the Legislature of Meghalaya by`
  line `law not to disqualify its holder; or`
  line
  line `(b) if he is of unsound mind any stands so declared by a competent court;`
  line
  line `(c) if he is an undischarged insolvent;`
  line
  line `(d) if he is not a citizen of India, or has voluntarily acquired the citizenship of a foreign State or is`
  line `under any acknowledgment of allegiance or adherence to a foreign State;`
  line
  line `(e) if he is so disqualified by or under any of the provisions of Chapter III of Part II of the`
  line `Representation of the People Act, 1951 (43 of 1951), as applied to and in relation to the`
  line `Legislative Assembly by section 17.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of this section, a person shall not be deemed to hold an office of profit under the`
  line `Government of India or the Government of any State or the Government of Meghalaya by reason only,`
  line `that he is a Minister either for the Union or for such State or for Meghalaya.`
  line
  line `(3) If any question arises as to whether a member has become disqualified for being such a member`
  line `under the provisions of sub-section (1), the question shall be referred for the decision of the Governor and`
  line `his decision shall be final.`
  line
  line `(4) Before giving any decision on any such question, the Governor shall obtain the opinion of the`
  line `Election Commission and shall act according to such opinion.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (39231)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Penalty for sitting and voting before making an oath or affirmation or when not qualified or when disqualified.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39231&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `If a person sits or votes as member of the Legislative Assembly before he has`
  line `complied with the requirements of section 26, or when he knows that he is not qualified or that he is`
  line `disqualified for membership thereof, or that he is prohibited from so doing by the provisions of any law`
  line `made by Parliament or the Legislature of Meghalaya, he shall be liable in respect of each day on which he`
  line `so sits or votes, to a penalty of five hundred rupees to be recovered as a debt due to Meghalaya.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (39181)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Powers, privileges, etc., of members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39181&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act and to the rules`
  line `and standing orders regulating the procedure of the Legislature of Meghalaya, there shall be freedom of`
  line `speech in the Legislative Assembly of Meghalaya.`
  line
  line `(2) No member of the Legislative Assembly of Meghalaya shall be liable to any proceedings in any`
  line `court in respect of anything said or any vote given by him in the Assembly or any committee thereof, and`
  line `no person shall be so liable in respect of the publication by or under the authority of the Assembly of any`
  line `report, paper, votes or proceedings.`
  line
  line `(3) In other respects, the powers, privileges and immunities of the Legislative Assembly and of the`
  line `members and the committees thereof shall be such as may from time to time be defined by the Legislature`
  line `of Meghalaya by law, and until so defined, shall be those for the time being enjoyed by the House of the`
  line `People and its members and committees.`
  line
  line `(4) The provisions of sub-sections (1), (2) and (3) shall apply in relation to persons who by virtue of`
  line `this Act have the right to speak in, or otherwise to take part in the proceedings of, the Legislative`
  line `Assembly or any committee thereof as they apply in relation to members of that Assembly.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (39182)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Salaries and allowances of members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39182&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `Members of the Legislative Assembly shall be entitled`
  line `to receive such salaries and allowances as may from time to time be determined by the Legislature of`
  line `Meghalaya by law and, until provision in that respect is so made, such salaries and allowances as the`
  line `Governor may, by order, determine.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (39183)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Extent of Legislative power.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39183&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Legislature of`
  line `Meghalaya has exclusive power to make laws for Meghalaya or any part thereof with respect to any of the`
  line `matters enumerated in Part A or Part B of the Second Schedule:`
  line
  line `Provided that the exclusive power of the Legislature of Meghalaya to make laws in so far as it relates`
  line `to that part of the area comprised within the municipality of Shillong as immediately before the`
  line `commencement of the Constitution formed part of the Khasi State of Mylliem, shall extend only to`
  line `matters with respect to which the District Council having authority in that area has power to make laws`
  line `(in whatever form it may be) immediately before the appointed day in exercise of any of the powers`
  line `conferred by the Sixth Schedule to the Constitution.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Legislature of Meghalaya and the Legislature of the`
  line `State of Assam also shall have power to make laws for Meghalaya or any part thereof with respect to any`
  line `of the matters enumerated in Part C of the Second Schedule:`
  line
  line `Provided that the power of the Legislature of Meghalaya to make any such law shall not extend to the`
  line `area comprised within the municipality of Shillong which immediately before the commencement of the`
  line `Constitution formed part of the Khasi State of Mylliem.`
  line
  line `(3) For the removal of doubt it is hereby declared that nothing in sub-section (1) or sub-section (2)`
  line `shall derogate from the powers conferred by the Constitution—`
  line
  line `(a) on Parliament to make laws for the whole or any part of the State of Assam, including`
  line `Meghalaya, with respect to any of the matters enumerated in the Second Schedule; or`
  line
  line `(b) on the Legislature of the State of Assam to make laws for the whole or any part of Assam,`
  line `including Meghalaya, with respect to any of the matters enumerated in List II or List II in the Seventh`
  line `Schedule to the Constitution, except in so far as any of the matters aforesaid falls within`
  line `sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (39234)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Exemption from taxation of properties of the Union and the State of Assam and of certain vehicles registered in Assam or Meghalaya.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39234&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) The property of the Union shall, save in so far as`
  line `Parliament may, by law, otherwise provide, be exempt from all taxes imposed by Meghalaya or by any`
  line `authority within Meghalaya.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in sub-section (1) shall, until Parliament by law otherwise provides, prevent any authority`
  line `within Meghalaya from levying any tax on any property of the Union to which such property was`
  line `immediately before the commencement of this Act liable or treated as liable so long as that tax continues`
  line `to be levied in Meghalaya.`
  line
  line `(3) The property of the State of Assam shall, so long as the property of Meghalaya in the rest of`
  line `Assam is exempt from taxes imposed by the Government of Assam or by any authority within the State of`
  line `Assam, be exempt from all taxes imposed by Meghalaya or by any authority within Meghalaya.`
  line
  line `(4) No vehicle registered at any place in the State of Assam, not being a place in Meghalaya, and`
  line `transiting through Meghalaya shall be liable to any tax under any law enacted by the Legislature of`
  line `Meghalaya so long as any vehicle registered at any place in Meghalaya and transiting through the territory`
  line `of Assam (not comprised in Meghalaya) is exempt from payment of any tax under any law enacted by the`
  line `Legislature of the State of Assam.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (39235)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Inconsistency between laws made by Parliament and laws made by the Legislature of Meghalaya.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39235&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any provision of a law made by the Legislature of Meghalaya is repugnant to any`
  line `provision of a law made by Parliament which Parliament is competent to enact, or to any provision of any`
  line `existing law with respect to one of the matters enumerated in the Concurrent List in the Seventh Schedule`
  line `to the Constitution, then, subject to the provisions of sub-section (2), the law made by Parliament,`
  line `whether passed before or after the law, made by the Legislature of Meghalaya, or, as the case may be, the`
  line `existing law, shall prevail and the law made by the Legislature of Meghalaya shall, to the extent of the`
  line `repugnancy, be void.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a law made by the Legislature of Meghalaya with respect to one of the matters enumerated`
  line `in the Concurrent List in the Seventh Schedule to the Constitution, which the Legislature of Meghalaya is`
  line `competent to enact under this Act contains any provision repugnant to the provision of an earlier law`
  line `made by Parliament or an existing law with respect to that matter, then, the law so made by the`
  line `Legislature of Meghalaya shall, if it has been reserved for the consideration of the President and has`
  line `received his assent, prevail in Meghalaya:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall prevent Parliament from enacting at any time, any law`
  line `with respect to the same matter, including a law adding to, amending, varying or repealing the law so`
  line `made by the Legislature of Meghalaya.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (39236)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Inconsistency between laws made by the Legislature of the State of Assam and laws made by the Legislature of Meghalaya.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39236&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `Where a law made by the Legislature of Meghalaya with respect to one`
  line `of the matters enumerated in Part C of the Second Schedule contains any provisions repugnant to the`
  line `provision of an earlier law made by the Legislature of the State of Assam which that Legislature is`
  line `competent to enact, or to any provision of any existing law with respect to that matter, then, the law so`
  line `made by the Legislature of Meghalaya shall, to the extent of the repugnancy, be void unless the law has`
  line `received assent under section 39 after the Governor has obtained the advice of the Chief Minister of`
  line `Assam:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this section shall prevent the Legislature of the State of Assam`
  line `from enacting at any time any law with respect to the same matter including a law adding to, amending,`
  line `varying or repealing the law so made by the Legislature of Meghalaya.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.—In this section and in sections 35 and 59, "existing law" means any law, Ordinance,`
  line `order, bye-law, rule or regulation passed or made before the appointed day by any Legislature, authority`
  line `or person having power to make such a law, Ordinance, order, bye-law, rule or regulation.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.—In this section and in sections 39 and 50, the reference to the advice of the`
  line `Chief Minister of Assam shall, while a Proclamation issued in relation to the State of Assam under clause`
  line `(1) of article 356 of the Constitution is in operation, be construed as a reference to the instructions from`
  line `the President.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (39187)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Special provisions as to financial Bills.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39187&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Bill or amendment shall not be introduced into,`
  line `or moved in, the Legislative Assembly except on the recommendations of the Governor if such Bill or`
  line `amendment makes provisions dealing with any of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the imposition, abolition, remission, alteration or regulation of any tax;`
  line
  line `(b) the regulation of the borrowing of money or the giving of any guarantee by Meghalaya or the`
  line `amendment of the law with respect to any financial obligations undertaken or to be undertaken by`
  line Meghalaya;
  line
  line `(c) the custody of the Consolidated Fund or the Contingency Fund of Meghalaya, the payment of`
  line `moneys into, or withdrawal of moneys from, any such Fund;`
  line
  line `(d) the appropriation of moneys out of the Consolidated Fund of Meghalaya;`
  line
  line `(e) the declaring of any expenditure to be expenditure charged on the Consolidated Fund of`
  line `Meghalaya, or the increasing of the amount of any such expenditure;`
  line
  line `(f) the receipt of money on account of the Consolidated Fund of Meghalaya or the public account`
  line `of Meghalaya or the custody or issue of such money:`
  line
  line `Provided that no recommendation shall be required under this sub-section for the moving of an`
  line `amendment making provision for the reduction or abolition of any tax.`
  line
  line `(2) A Bill or amendment shall not be deemed to make provision for any of the matters specified in`
  line `sub-section (1) by reason only that it provides for the imposition of fines or other pecuniary penalties, or`
  line `for the demand or payment of fees for licences or fees for services rendered, or by reason that it provides`
  line `for the imposition, abolition, remission, alteration or regulation of any tax by any local authority or body`
  line `for local purposes.`
  line
  line `(3) A Bill, which, if enacted and brought into operation, would involve expenditure from the`
  line `Consolidated Fund of Meghalaya shall not be passed by the Legislative Assembly unless the Governor`
  line `has recommended to the Assembly the consideration of the Bill.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (39188)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Procedure as to lapsing of Bills.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39188&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `A Bill pending in the Legislative Assembly shall not lapse by`
  line `reason of the prorogation of the Assembly, but shall lapse on a dissolution thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (39189)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Assent to Bills.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39189&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `When a Bill has been passed by the Legislative Assembly, it shall be presented`
  line `to the Governor and the Governor shall declare either that he assents to the Bill or that he withholds`
  line `assent therefrom or that he reserves the Bill for the consideration of the President:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Governor may, as soon as possible after the presentation to him of the Bill for`
  line `assent, return the Bill if it is not a Money Bill together with a message requesting that the`
  line `Legislative Assembly will reconsider the Bill or any specified provisions thereof and, in particular, will`
  line `consider the desirability of introducing any such amendments as he may recommend in his message and,`
  line `when a Bill is so returned, the Legislative Assembly shall reconsider the Bill accordingly, and if the Bill`
  line `is passed again by the Assembly with or without amendment and presented to the Governor for assent, the`
  line `Governor shall not--`
  line
  line `(a) give assent in the case of a Bill containing provisions of the nature referred to in section 36`
  line `except after obtaining the advice of the Chief Minister of Assam;`
  line
  line `(b) withhold assent in the case of any other Bill.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section and section 40 a Bill shall be deemed to be a Money`
  line `Bill if it contains only provisions dealing with all or any of the matters specified in sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 37 or any matter incidental to any of those matters and there is endorsed thereon the certificate of`
  line `the Speaker of the Legislative Assembly signed by him that it is a Money Bill:`
  line
  line `Provided that a Bill shall not be deemed to be a Money Bill by reason only that it provides for the`
  line `imposition of fines or other pecuniary penalties, or for the demand or payment of fees for licences or fees`
  line `for services rendered or by reason that it provides for the imposition, abolition, remission, alteration or`
  line `regulation of any tax by any local authority or body for local purposes.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (39190)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Bills reserved for consideration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39190&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `When a Bill is reserved by the Governor for the consideration`
  line `of the President, the President shall declare either that he assents to the Bill or that he withholds assent`
  line `therefrom:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the Bill is not a Money Bill, the President may direct the Governor to return the`
  line `Bill to the Legislative Assembly together with such a message as is referred to in section 39, and when a`
  line `Bill is so returned, the Legislative Assembly shall reconsider it accordingly within a period of six months`
  line `from the date of receipt of such message, and if it is again passed by the Legislative Assembly with or`
  line `without amendment, it shall be presented again to the President for his consideration.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (39191)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Requirements as to sanction and recommendation to be regarded as matters of procedure only.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39191&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `No Act of the Legislature of Meghalaya and no provision in any such Act shall be invalid by`
  line `reason only that some recommendation or previous sanction required by the Constitution or this Act was`
  line `not given, if assent to that Act was given—`
  line
  line `(a) where the recommendation required was that of the Governor, either by the Governor or by`
  line `the President;`
  line
  line `(b) where the recommendation or previous sanction required was that of the President, by the`
  line President.
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (39192)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Annual Financial Statement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39192&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Governor shall in respect of every financial year cause to`
  line `be laid before the Legislative Assembly a statement of the estimated receipts and expenditure of`
  line `Meghalaya for that year, hereinafter referred to as "the annual financial, statement".`
  line
  line `(2) The estimates of expenditure embodied in the annual financial statement shall show separately—`
  line
  line `(a) the sums required to meet expenditure described by this Act as expenditure charged upon the`
  line `Consolidated Fund of Meghalaya; and`
  line
  line `(b) the sums required to meet other expenditure proposed to be made from the Consolidated Fund`
  line `of Meghalaya,`
  line
  line `and shall distinguish expenditure on revenue account from other expenditure.`
  line
  line `(3) The following expenditure shall be expenditure charged upon the Consolidated Fund of`
  line Meghalaya—
  line
  line `(a) the salaries and allowances of the Speaker and the Deputy Speaker of the`
  line `Legislative Assembly;`
  line
  line `(b) debt charges for which the autonomous State is liable including interest sinking fund charges`
  line `and redemption charges, and other expenditure relating to the raising of loans and the service and`
  line `redemption of debt;`
  line
  line `(c) any sums required to satisfy any judgment, decree or award of any court or arbitral tribunal;`
  line and
  line
  line `(d) any other expenditure declared by the Constitution or by the Legislature of Meghalaya to be`
  line `so charged.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (39193)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Procedure in Legislative Assembly with respect to estimates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39193&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `(1) So much of the estimates as`
  line `relates to expenditure charged upon the Consolidated Fund of Meghalaya shall not be submitted to the`
  line `vote of the Legislative Assembly, but nothing in this sub-section shall be construed as preventing the`
  line `discussion in the Legislative Assembly of any of those estimates.`
  line
  line `(2) So much of the said estimates as relates to other expenditure shall be submitted in the form of`
  line `demands for grants to the Legislative Assembly, and the Legislative Assembly shall have power to assent,`
  line `or to refuse to assent, to any demand, or to assent to any demand subject to a reduction of the amount`
  line `specified therein.`
  line
  line `(3) No demand for a grant shall be made except on the recommendation of the Governor.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (39194)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Appropriation Bills.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39194&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `(1) As soon as may be after the grants under section 43 have been made`
  line `by the Legislative Assembly, there shall be introduced a Bill to provide for the appropriation out of the`
  line `Consolidated Fund of Meghalaya of all moneys required to meet—`
  line
  line `(a) the grants so made by the Legislative Assembly; and`
  line
  line `(b) the expenditure charged on the Consolidated Fund of Meghalaya,`
  line
  line `but not exceeding in any case the amount shown in the statement previously laid before the Assembly.`
  line
  line `(2) No amendment shall be proposed to any such Bill in the Legislative Assembly which will have the`
  line `effect of varying the amount or altering the destination of any grant so made or of varying the amount of`
  line `any expenditure charged on the Consolidated Fund of Meghalaya, and the decision of the person`
  line `presiding as to whether an amendment is inadmissible under this sub-section shall be final.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the provisions of sections 45 and 46, no money shall be withdrawn from the`
  line `Consolidated Fund of Meghalaya except under appropriation made by law passed in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (39195)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Supplementary, additional or excess grants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39195&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Governor shall,--`
  line
  line `(a) if the amount authorised by any law made in accordance with the provisions of section 44 to`
  line `be expended for a particular service for the current financial year is found to be insufficient for the`
  line `purposes of that year or when a need has arisen during the current financial year for supplementary or`
  line `additional expenditure upon some new service not contemplated in the annual financial statement for`
  line `that year, or`
  line
  line `(b) if any money has been spent on any service during a financial year in excess of the amount`
  line `granted for that service and for that year,`
  line
  line `cause to be laid before the Legislative Assembly another statement showing the estimated amount of that`
  line `expenditure or cause to be presented to the Legislative Assembly a demand for such excess, as the case`
  line `may be.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of sections 42, 43 and 44 shall have effect in relation to any such statement and`
  line `expenditure or demand and also to any law to be made authorising the appropriation of moneys out of the`
  line `Consolidated Fund of Meghalaya to meet such expenditure or the grant in respect of such demand as they`
  line `have effect in relation to the annual financial statement and the expenditure mentioned therein or to a`
  line `demand for a grant and the law to be made for the authorisation of appropriation of moneys out of the`
  line `Consolidated Fund of Meghalaya to meet such expenditure or grant.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (39196)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Votes on Account and exceptional grant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39196&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything in the foregoing`
  line `provisions of this Part, the Legislative Assembly shall have power—`
  line
  line `(a) to make any grant in advance in respect of the estimated expenditure for a part of any`
  line `financial year pending the completion of the procedure prescribed in section 43 for the voting of such`
  line `grant and the passing of the law in accordance with the provisions of section 44 in relation to that`
  line expenditure;
  line
  line `(b) to make a grant for meeting an unexpected demand upon the resources of the autonomous`
  line `State when on account of the magnitude or the indefinite character of the service the demand cannot`
  line `be stated with the details ordinarily given in the annual financial statement;`
  line
  line `(c) to make an exceptional grant which forms no part of the current service of any financial year;`
  line
  line `and the Legislature of Meghalaya shall have power to authorise by law the withdrawal of moneys from`
  line `the Consolidated Fund of Meghalaya for the purpose for which the said grants are made.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of sections 43 and 44 shall have effect in relation to the making of any grant under`
  line `sub-section (1) and to any law to be made under that sub-section as they have effect in relation to the`
  line `making of a grant with regard to any expenditure mentioned in the annual financial statement and the law`
  line `to be made for the authorisation of appropriation of moneys out of the Consolidated Fund of Meghalaya`
  line `to meet such expenditure.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (39197)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Rules of procedure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39197&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Legislative Assembly may make rules for regulating, subject to the`
  line `provisions of this Act, its procedure and the conduct of its business including the language or languages`
  line `to be used in the Legislative Assembly.`
  line
  line `(2) Until rules are made under sub-section (1), the rules of procedure and standing orders with respect`
  line `to the Legislative Assembly of the State of Assam in force immediately before the commencement of this`
  line `Act shall have effect in relation to the Legislative Assembly subject to such modifications and adaptations`
  line `as may be made therein by the Governor.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (39198)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Restrictions on discussion in the Legislative Assembly.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39198&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `No discussion shall take place in the`
  line `Legislative Assembly with respect to the conduct of any Judge of the Supreme Court, or of a High Court,`
  line `in the discharge of his duties.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (39199)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Courts not to enquire into the proceedings of Legislative Assembly.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39199&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `(1) The validity of any`
  line `proceedings in the Legislative Assembly shall not be called in question on the ground of any alleged`
  line `irregularity of procedure.`
  line
  line `(2) No officer or member of the Legislative Assembly in whom powers are vested by or under this`
  line `Act for regulating procedure or the conduct of business or for maintaining order, in the`
  line `Legislative Assembly shall be subject to the jurisdiction of any court in respect of the exercise by him of`
  line `those powers.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (39200)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Power of Governor to promulgate Ordinances during recess of Legislative Assembly.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39200&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `(1) If`
  line `at any time, except when the Legislative Assembly is in session, the Governor is satisfied that`
  line `circumstances exist which render it necessary for him to take immediate action, he may promulgate such`
  line `Ordinance as the circumstances appear to him to require:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Governor shall not without instructions from the President, promulgate any such`
  line `Ordinance, if—`
  line
  line `(a) a Bill containing the same provisions would under the Constitution or this Act have required`
  line `the previous sanction of the President for the introduction thereof into the Legislative Assembly of`
  line `Meghalaya; or`
  line
  line `(b) he would have deemed it necessary to reserve a Bill containing the same provisions for the`
  line `consideration of the President; or`
  line
  line `(c) an Act of the Legislature of Meghalaya containing the same provisions would under this Act`
  line `have been invalid unless, having been reserved for the consideration of the President, it had received`
  line `the assent of the President:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Governor shall not, except on the advice of the Chief Minister of Assam,`
  line `promulgate any such Ordinance if with respect to a Bill containing the same provisions he would have`
  line `deemed it necessary under this Act to obtain the advice of the Chief Minister before assenting thereto.`
  line
  line `(2) An Ordinance promulgated under this section shall have the same force and effect as an Act of the`
  line `Legislative Assembly assented to by the Governor, but every such Ordinance—`
  line
  line `(a) shall be laid before Legislative Assembly and shall cease to operate at the expiration of six`
  line `weeks from the reassembly of the Legislative Assembly or if before the expiration of that period a`
  line `resolution disapproving it is passed by the Legislative Assembly, upon the passing of the resolution`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) may be withdrawn at any time by the Governor.`
  line
  line `(3) If and so far as an Ordinance under this section makes any provision which would not be valid if`
  line `enacted in an Act of the Legislature of Meghalaya assented to by the Governor, it shall be void:`
  line
  line `Provided that—`
  line
  line `(a) for the purposes of section 35 relating to the effect of an Act of the Legislature of Meghalaya`
  line `which is repugnant to an Act of Parliament or an existing law with respect to a matter enumerated in`
  line `the Concurrent List in the Seventh Schedule to the Constitution, an Ordinance promulgated under this`
  line `section in pursuance of instructions from the President shall be deemed to be an Act of the Legislature`
  line `which has been reserved for the consideration of the President and assented to by him;`
  line
  line `(b) for the purposes of section 36 relating to the effect of an Act of the Legislature of Meghalaya`
  line `which is repugnant to an Act of the Legislature of the State of Assam or an existing law with respect`
  line `to a matter enumerated in Part C of the Second Schedule, an Ordinance promulgated under this`
  line `section on the advice of the Chief Minister of Assam shall be deemed to be an Act of the Legislature`
  line `which has been assented to on the advice of the Chief Minister.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (39201)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Consolidated Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39201&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of section 52, all revenue received by the`
  line `Government of Meghalaya, all loans raised by that Government by the issue of treasury bills, loans or`
  line `ways and means advances and all moneys received by that Government in repayment of loans shall form`
  line `one consolidated fund to be entitled "the Consolidated Fund of Meghalaya".`
  line
  line `(2) All other public moneys received by or on behalf of the Government of Meghalaya shall be`
  line `credited to the public account of Meghalaya.`
  line
  line `(3) No moneys out of the Consolidated Fund of Meghalaya shall be appropriated except in`
  line `accordance with law and for the purposes and in the manner provided in this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (39202)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title `Contingency Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39202&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `The Legislature of Meghalaya may, by law, establish a Contingency Fund`
  line `in the nature of an imprest to be entitled "the Contingency Fund of Meghalaya" into which shall be paid`
  line `from time to time such sums as may be determined by such law, and the said Fund shall be placed at the`
  line `disposal of the Governor to enable advances to be made by him out of such Fund for the purposes of`
  line `meeting unforeseen expenditure pending authorisation of such expenditure by the Legislature of`
  line `Meghalaya by law under section 45 or section 46.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (39203)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title `Custody of suitors' deposits and other moneys received by public servants and courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39203&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line All
  line `moneys received by or deposited with—`
  line
  line `(a) any officer employed in connection with the affairs of Meghalaya in his capacity as such,`
  line `other than revenues or public moneys raised or received by the Government of Meghalaya; or`
  line
  line `(b) any court within Meghalaya to the credit of any cause, matter, account or persons shall be`
  line `paid into the public account of Meghalaya.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (43689)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `Custody, etc., of Consolidated Fund, Contingency Fund and moneys credited to the public account`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=43689&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `The custody of the Consolidated Fund and the Contingency Fund of Meghalaya, the payment`
  line `of moneys into such Funds, the withdrawal of moneys therefrom, the custody of public moneys other than`
  line `those credited to such Funds received by or on behalf of the Government of Meghalaya, their payment`
  line `into the public account of Meghalaya and the withdrawal of moneys from such account and all other`
  line `matters connected with or ancillary to matters aforesaid shall be regulated by law made by the Legislature`
  line `of Meghalaya, and, until provision in that behalf is so made, shall be regulated by rules made by the`
  line Governor.
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (39205)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Certain taxes levied by Assam to be appropriated by Meghalaya.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39205&sectionno=55&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in this Act, any tax on the consumption or sale of electricity relatable to entry 53 in`
  line `the State List in the Seventh Schedule to the Constitution, and any tax on the sale or purchase of goods`
  line `relatable to entry 54 in the said List levied by the Government of Assam shall be collected within`
  line `Meghalaya but not including any area comprised within the municipality of Shillong by the Government`
  line `of Meghalaya, and the proceeds in any financial year of any such tax leviable within Meghalaya shall not`
  line `form part of the Consolidated Fund of Assam, but shall form part of the Consolidated Fund of Meghalaya.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a tax relatable to entry 54 in the State List aforesaid levied by the Government of Assam is`
  line `collected by that Government at the first point of sale or purchase of goods, such portion of the tax so`
  line `collected as may be agreed upon by the Governments of Assam and Meghalaya or in default of such`
  line `agreement, as such the Central Government may determine, shall be payable to Meghalaya.`
  line
  line `(3) The laws with respect to the taxes referred to in sub-section (1) shall have effect subject to such`
  line `exceptions and modifications as the Central Government, may, by order, specify for the purpose of giving`
  line `effect to the provisions of that sub-section.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (39206)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 56
  title `Distribution of revenues.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39206&sectionno=56&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `(1) The grants-in-aid under clause (1) of article 275 and the share of`
  line `the taxes on income, the distributable Union duties of excise, the additional duties of excise on goods of`
  line `special importance and estate duty payable to the State of Assam under the Constitution (Distribution of`
  line `Revenues) Order, 1969, the Union Duties of Excise (Distribution) Act, 1962 (3 of 1962), the Additional`
  line `Duties of Excise (Goods of Special Importance) Act, 1957 (58 of 1957) and the Estate Duty (Distribution)`
  line `Act, 1962 (9 of 1962), shall be construed as from the appointed day, as payable to the State of Assam and`
  line `the autonomous State of Meghalaya in such proportion as the President may, by order, determine.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made by the President under sub-section (1) shall be laid before Parliament as soon as`
  line `may be after it is made.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (39207)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 57
  title `Authorisation of expenditure pending its sanction by Legislative Assembly.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39207&sectionno=57&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `The Governor`
  line `may, at any time before the appointed day, authorise such expenditure from the Consolidated Fund of`
  line `Meghalaya as he deems necessary for a period of not more than six months beginning with the appointed`
  line `day pending the sanction of that expenditure by the Legislative Assembly:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Governor may, after the appointed day, authorise such further expenditure as he`
  line `deems necessary from the Consolidated Fund of Meghalaya for any period not extending beyond the said`
  line `period of six months.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (39208)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 58
  title `Apportionment of assets and liabilities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39208&sectionno=58&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `The assets and liabilities of the State of Assam`
  line `immediately before the appointed day shall be apportioned between that State and Meghalaya in`
  line `accordance with the provisions contained in the Third Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (39209)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 59
  title `Obligation of Meghalaya, the State of Assam and the Union.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39209&sectionno=59&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `The executive power of`
  line `Meghalaya shall be so exercised as to ensure compliance with the laws made by Parliament, the`
  line `Legislature of the State of Assam and any existing laws which apply in Meghalaya, and the executive`
  line `power of the Union and of the State of Assam shall extend to the giving of such directions to Meghalaya`
  line `as may appear to the Government of India or the Government of Assam, as the case may be, to be`
  line `necessary for that purpose.`
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (39210)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 60
  title `Control over the autonomous State in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39210&sectionno=60&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `The executive power of Meghalaya shall`
  line `be so exercised as not to impede or prejudice the exercise of the executive power of the Union or the`
  line `Government of Assam, as the case may be, and the executive power of the Union and the State of Assam`
  line `shall extend to the giving of such directions to Meghalaya as may appear to the Government of India or`
  line `the Government of Assam, as the case may be, to be necessary for that purpose.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (39211)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 61
  title `Entrustment of functions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39211&sectionno=61&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything in this Act,—`
  line
  line `(a) the Government of Assam may, with the consent of the Government of Meghalaya, entrust`
  line `either conditionally or unconditionally to that Government or to its officers function in relation to any`
  line `matter to which the executive power of the State of Assam extends;`
  line
  line `(b) the Government of Meghalaya may, with the consent for the Government of Assam, entrust`
  line `either conditionally or unconditionally to that Government or to its officers functions in relation to`
  line `any matter to which the executive power of Meghalaya extends.`
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (39212)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 62
  title `Provisions as to Provisional Legislative Assembly.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39212&sectionno=62&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `(1) Until the Legislative Assembly of`
  line `Meghalaya has been duly constituted and summoned to meet for the first session under the provisions of`
  line `Part III, there shall be a Provisional Legislative Assembly which shall consist of not less than thirty-five`
  line `and not more than fifty-five persons as the Central Government may, after consultation with the Election`
  line `Commission, by order, determine, and such persons shall be elected in the manner specified in`
  line `sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (1), the members of the Provisional Legislative Assembly`
  line `shall be elected in the following manner, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) there shall be an electoral college for each autonomous district within Meghalaya which shall`
  line `consist of the elected members of the District Council thereof, and each electoral college shall elect`
  line `such number of persons to the Provisional Legislative Assembly as the President may, after`
  line `consultation with the Election Commission, by order, determine;`
  line
  line `(b) the election of members to the Provisional Legislative Assembly shall be in accordance with`
  line `the system of proportional representation by means of the single transferable vote and shall be subject`
  line `to such rules as the Central Government may, after consultation with the Election Commission, make`
  line `in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may nominate to the Provisional Legislative Assembly not more than`
  line `three persons not being persons in the service of the Government, to represent any minority communities`
  line `in Meghalaya which, in its opinion, need representation in the Assembly.`
  line
  line `(4) No person shall be qualified to be chosen as a member of the Provisional Legislative Assembly`
  line `unless he is a person whose name is for the time being entered in the electoral roll for so much of any`
  line `constituency of the Legislative Assembly of Assam as is comprised within Meghalaya and is not less than`
  line `twenty-five years of age.`
  line
  line `(5) If owing to death, resignation or otherwise, the office of a member of the Provisional Legislative`
  line `Assembly falls vacant, it may be filled up as soon as practicable under and in accordance with the`
  line `foregoing provisions of this section.`
  line
  line `(6) The term of office of the members of the Provisional Legislative Assembly shall expire`
  line `immediately before the first meeting of the Legislative Assembly duly constituted under this Act.`
  line
  line `(7) The election by the electoral college under this section shall not be called in question on the`
  line `ground merely of the existence of a vacancy in the membership of any District Council forming part of`
  line `the electoral college.`
  line
  line `(8) The Provisional Legislative Assembly constituted under this section shall, for so long it is in`
  line `existence, be deemed to be the Legislative Assembly duly constituted under this Act, and accordingly the`
  line `provisions of Part III shall, so far as may be, apply in relation to the Provisional Legislative Assembly as`
  line `they apply in relation to the Legislative Assembly.`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (39213)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 63
  title `Special Committee for development of Shillong.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39213&sectionno=63&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, in consultation`
  line `with the Governments of Assam and Meghalaya, by order, constitute a committee consisting of such`
  line `number of persons as it may think fit for advising the two Governments on matters of common interests`
  line `with respect to Shillong in the field of education and water supply in particular, and with respect to its`
  line `development and administration in general.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—In this section, Shillong shall mean the areas comprised within the cantonment and`
  line `municipality of Shillong and include such other areas adjoining the said cantonment or Municipality as`
  line `may be agreed upon by the Governments of Assam and Meghalaya in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (39214)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 64
  title `Provisions as to continuance of courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39214&sectionno=64&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `All courts and tribunals and all authorities discharging`
  line `lawful functions throughout Meghalaya or any part thereof immediately before the appointed day shall,`
  line `unless their continuance is inconsistent with the provisions of this Act or until other provision is made by`
  line `a competent authority, continue to exercise their respective functions.`
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (39215)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 65
  title `Provisions relating to services.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39215&sectionno=65&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person who being a member of an All-India Service`
  line `is for the time being borne on the Assam State Cadre of that Service or is otherwise serving in connection`
  line `with the affairs of the State of Assam as a member of Class I service of that State may be required by the`
  line `Government of that State to serve in connection with the affairs of Meghalaya for such period or periods`
  line `as the Government of Assam may, by order, direct:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made`
  line
  line `(a) before the appointed day, except with the approval of the Central Government; and`
  line
  line `(b) on or after the appointed day, except in accordance with such rules as may be made by the`
  line `Central Government after consultation with the Governments of Assam and Meghalaya.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to any general or special order which the Central Government may make in this behalf,`
  line `the control over any such person as is referred to in sub-section (1) shall, for so long as he is required to`
  line `serve in connection with the affairs of Meghalaya, be vested in the Government of Meghalaya.`
  line
  line `(3) Such persons serving in connection with the affairs of the State of Assam immediately before the`
  line `appointed day, not being a person referred to in sub-section (1) as may be determined by agreement, between the Government of Assam and the Government of Meghalaya or in default of agreement, by the`
  line `Central Government, may, notwithstanding anything in the terms of their appointments or their conditions`
  line `of service, be required to serve in connection with the affairs of the autonomous State.`
  line
  line `(4) All previous service rendered by a person referred to in sub-section (3) in connection with the`
  line `affairs of the State of Assam shall be deemed to have been rendered in connection with the affairs of the`
  line `autonomous State for the purposes of the rules regulating his conditions of service.`
  line
  line `(5) Nothing in sub-sections (3) and (4) shall be deemed to affect the power of the Legislature of`
  line `Meghalaya or the Governor to determine the conditions of service of persons serving in connection with`
  line `the affairs of Meghalaya:`
  line
  line `Provided that the conditions of service applicable immediately before the appointed day to any person`
  line `referred to in sub-section (3) shall not be varied to his disadvantage except with the previous approval of`
  line `the Government of Assam.`
obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (39216)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 66
  title `Continuance of existing laws and their adaptations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39216&sectionno=66&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `(1) All laws in force immediately before`
  line `the appointed day in the autonomous State shall continue to be in force therein until altered, repealed or`
  line `amended by a competent legislature or other competent authority.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purpose of facilitating the application in relation to the autonomous State of any law made`
  line `before the appointed day, the appropriate Government may, within two years from that day, by order,`
  line `make such adaptations or modifications of the law, whether by way of repeal or amendment, as may be`
  line `necessary or expedient and thereupon every such law shall have effect subject to the adaptations and`
  line `modifications so made until altered, repealed or amended by a competent legislature or other competent`
  line authority.
  line
  line `Explanation.—In this section, the expression "appropriate Government" means as respects any law`
  line `relating to a matter enumerated in the Union List in the Seventh Schedule to the Constitution, the`
  line `Central Government, as respects any law relating to a matter in the Second Schedule, the Government of`
  line `Meghalaya, and, as respects any other law, the Government of Assam.`
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (39217)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 67
  title `Autonomous State to be a State for certain purposes of the Constitution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39217&sectionno=67&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the`
  line `other provisions contained in this Act, reference to a State (by whatever form of words) in any of the`
  line `following articles of the Constitution shall be construed as including a reference to the autonomous State,`
  line `namely:—`
  line
  line `Articles 12 to 15 (inclusive), 16 [except clause (3) thereof], 18, 19, 23, 25, 28 to 31 (inclusive),`
  line `31A, 34 to 51 (inclusive), 58, 59, 66, 73, 102, 110(1)(f), 131, 138, 149, 150, 151, 161, 209, 210, 233,`
  line `234, 235, 237, 251, 252, 256 to 258A (inclusive), 261, 262, 263, 268, 269, 270, 272, 274 to 280`
  line `(inclusive), 282, 288, 289, 293, 296, 298 to 305 (inclusive), 308 to 311 (inclusive), 320, 323(2), 324`
  line `to 329 (inclusive), 339 to 342 (inclusive), 345 to 348 (inclusive), 350, 350A, 350B, 353, 355 to 358`
  line `(inclusive), 360, 361, 364 to 367 (inclusive).`
  line
  line `Explanation.—Reference in any of the articles above specified to the High Court or to the`
  line `State Public Service Commission shall be construed as reference to the High Court of Assam or the`
  line `Public Service Commission of the State of Assam, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (39218)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 68
  title `Power of Governments of Assam and Meghalaya to carry on trade, etc., in Meghalaya.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39218&sectionno=68&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `(1) The executive power which the Government of Assam may exercise under article 298`
  line `in Meghalaya for the carrying on of any trade or business and for the acquisition, holding and disposal of`
  line `property and the making of contracts for any purpose shall, in so far as such trade or business or such`
  line `purpose is not one with respect to which the Legislature of the State of Assam may make laws, be subject`
  line `to legislation by the Legislature of Meghalaya.`
  line
  line `(2) The executive power which the Government of Meghalaya may exercise under article 298 in`
  line `Meghalaya for the carrying on of any trade or business and for the acquisition, holding and disposal of`
  line `property and the making of contracts of for any purpose shall, in so far as such trade or business or such`
  line `purpose is not one with respect to which the Legislature of Mehgalaya may make laws, be subject also to`
  line `legislation by the Legislature of the State of Assam.`
obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (39219)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 69
  title `Power to suspend provisions of this Act in case of failure of constitutional machinery.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39219&sectionno=69&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `Where a Proclamation is issued under article 356 in respect of Meghalaya, the President`
  line `may, by the same Proclamation or a subsequent Proclamation varying it, suspend also, in whole or in part,`
  line `the operation of any of the provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (39237)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 70
  title `Construction of reference to "State" and "State Government" in other laws in relation to Meghalaya.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39237&sectionno=70&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `Without prejudice to the provisions of sections 66 and 71 the Central Government may,`
  line `after consulting the Government of Assam, by notification in the Official Gazette, declare that any`
  line `reference to a "State" in a Central Act specified in the notification shall, in its application to Meghalaya,`
  line `be construed as a reference to the whole or any part of Meghalaya and any reference to "State`
  line `Government" in a Central Act specified in the notification shall in its application to Meghalaya be`
  line `construed as a reference to the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (39221)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 71
  title `Power to construe laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39221&sectionno=71&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding that no provision or insufficient provision has been`
  line `made under section 66 for the adaptation of a law made before the appointed day, any court, tribunal or`
  line `authority required or empowered to enforce such law may, for the purpose of facilitating its application in`
  line `relation to the autonomous State, construe the law in such manner not affecting the substance as may be`
  line `necessary or proper in regard to the matter before the court, tribunal or authority, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (39222)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 72
  title `Effect of provisions of Act inconsistent with other laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39222&sectionno=72&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall have`
  line `effect notwithstanding anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other law.`
obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (39223)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 73
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39223&sectionno=73&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the President may, by order, do anything not inconsistent with such provisions which appears to`
  line `him to be necessary or expedient for the purpose of removing the difficulty.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid before both Houses of Parliament as soon as`
  line `may be after it is made.`
obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (39224)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 74
  title `Amendment of the Sixth Schedule.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39224&sectionno=74&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line `The Sixth Schedule in the Constitution shall stand`
  line `amended as specified in the Fourth Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (39225)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 75
  title `Amendment of Act 2 of 1934.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39225&sectionno=75&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line `In section 21A of the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934, in`
  line `sub-section (1) , after the words "any State", the brackets and words "(including the autonomous State of`
  line `Meghalaya)" shall be inserted.`
obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_76:
  sectionId (39226)
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 76
  title `Amendment of Act 37 of 1956.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39226&sectionno=76&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line `In section 16 of the States Reorganisation Act, 1956, in`
  line `sub-section (1) , for clause (d), the following clause shall be substituted, namely:—`
  line
  line `"(d) in the case of the Eastern Zone,—`
  line
  line `(i) the Chief Minister and another Minister of the autonomous State of Meghalaya to be`
  line `nominated by the Governor of Assam and if there is no Council of Ministers therein, not more`
  line `than two members from the autonomous State of Meghalaya to be nominated by the`
  line `President; and`
  line
  line `(ii) the person for the time being holding the office of the Adviser to the Governor of Assam`
  line `for Tribal areas.".`
obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (39227)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 77
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 4 of 1986, s. 2 and the Schedule, for certain words (w.e.f. 15-5-1986).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804&sectionId=39227&sectionno=77&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00045_196955_1517807324804
obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules to give effect to the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every rule made under this section shall be laid as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament, while it is in session for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one`
  line `session or ^1`
  line `[in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid], both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be, so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
